1
00:00:04,898 --> 00:00:10,733
Sometimes, Śrila Guru Mahārāj …

2
00:00:10,733 --> 00:00:18,568
It’s interesting, some things that
devotees, novices, neophytes,

3
00:00:18,568 --> 00:00:20,368
visiting his Maṭh,

4
00:00:20,368 --> 00:00:25,147
those who maybe had been initiated
for a year or two or a few,

5
00:00:25,271 --> 00:00:28,510
[Family Life with God]

6
00:00:29,095 --> 00:00:31,778
they sometimes express things

7
00:00:31,778 --> 00:00:34,647
about what they liked
about Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

8
00:00:34,647 --> 00:00:39,648
in a very, almost naive,
childlike, simplicity,

9
00:00:39,648 --> 00:00:45,815
—because, after all, from a spiritual
point of view, they’re babies …

10
00:00:45,815 --> 00:00:48,378
But they sometimes said things

11
00:00:48,378 --> 00:00:53,590
that captured the heart
of Śrila Guru Mahārāj

12
00:00:53,590 --> 00:00:56,398
that may have melted his heart.

13
00:00:56,398 --> 00:01:04,929
So, more than a few times,
he told at one meeting at the Maṭh

14
00:01:05,948 --> 00:01:13,363
where Śrīla Swāmī Mahārāj Prabhupād
had sent his disciples

15
00:01:13,363 --> 00:01:17,100
—perhaps for the appearance day
of his Guru Mahārāj,

16
00:01:17,100 --> 00:01:19,775
their Guru Mahārāj,
Śrīla Saraswatī Ṭhākur,

17
00:01:19,775 --> 00:01:26,375
some such occasion—he sent his disciples
to Śrī Chaitanya Sāraswat Maṭh,

18
00:01:26,375 --> 00:01:32,315
and different people
were asked to speak.

19
00:01:32,315 --> 00:01:35,427
And one lady spoke,
and what she spoke

20
00:01:35,427 --> 00:01:40,011
left a lasting impression
upon Śrīla Guru Mahārāj.

21
00:01:40,011 --> 00:01:42,056
And what she said was,

22
00:01:42,056 --> 00:01:47,314
in expressing her appreciation
for Kṛṣṇa consciousness, she said,

23
00:01:47,314 --> 00:01:54,316
“We’re being given the opportunity
to have a family life with Kṛṣṇa.

24
00:01:54,316 --> 00:01:56,863
That’s what I like!

25
00:01:56,863 --> 00:02:02,202
That opportunity is before us. We can
have a family life with God himself!

26
00:02:02,202 --> 00:02:09,291
That possibility, that prospect,
inspires me.

27
00:02:09,291 --> 00:02:14,315
I’m thrilled at the potential
of that sort of prospect.”

28
00:02:14,315 --> 00:02:22,301
So maybe that lady 
was not a philosopher,

29
00:02:22,301 --> 00:02:29,482
someone who could quote
Vedic literature extensively,

30
00:02:29,482 --> 00:02:35,333
but what she expressed touched
the heart of Śrīla Guru Mahārāj.

31
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:41,114
And it really goes to the core
of Kṛṣṇa conception,

32
00:02:41,114 --> 00:02:44,898
that really that’s what we want,

33
00:02:44,898 --> 00:02:47,982
we want to have 
a loving relationship with Kṛṣṇa.

